<p>SECTION 4 THE CHOICE</p>
<p>None of us have ever seen an atom without a device that takes an 
image. Most of us have not attempted the calculations to understand the 
theory of gravity and the way it holds the moon in the sky. We do not 
calculate the stress of a bridge before we drive on it to make sure it 
will not collapse. Nor do we understand with certainty the way our water
 is cleaned, or our electricity is run before we drink it or we use it. 
How do we know for ourselves that these things are working properly? How
 do we know that the scientific theories we’ve been told are true?</p>
<p>We don’t. Not individually.</p>
<p>To know these things, we must survive on trust. As we grow out of 
ignorance, we trust that those who are wiser than us will guide us to 
the proper conclusions so that we can throw our stone further than those
 who came before us. We build our societies through 
social-knowledge-networks where each connected person can only know so 
much. We have hope that other people, strangers even, will be able to 
pick up the slack of our deficiencies.<br>
No matter how smart we are or how quickly we learn, we cannot know 
everything in this life. There is so much information that we don’t 
individually have the resources to process it all. We’re constrained by 
such things as time, brain power, money, and the physical resources 
necessary to carry out experiments. If we tried to learn everything the 
world has to offer, we would inevitably die before we could finish. This
 means that to move forward, we have to trust that other people can tell
 us what we don’t know without us having to do as much work as they did 
figuring it out.</p>
<p>Is this not faith?</p></div></div></div></div><div class="Message_messageMetadataContainer__nBPq7"><span class="Message_messageMetadataText__FxY5_">5:33 AM</span></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="ChatMessage_chatMessage__xkgHx" data-complete="true" id="message-230692238293"><div class="LeftSideMessageHeader_leftSideMessageHeader__5CfdD"><div class="LeftSideMessageHeader_headerWrapper__EpVkV"><div class="BotMessageHeader_wrapper__gvvdw"><a class="BotHeader_title__cURS_" target="_blank" href=""><div class="Avatar_root__rwLF0 Avatar_rounded__qlug0 Avatar_xx-sm__hwmu_" data-pdl-avatar=""><img alt="Bot image for BotORFQ3TYM2O" data-deleted="true" loading="lazy" width="20" height="20" decoding="async" data-nimg="1" style="color: transparent;" src="Hello%20Gemini%2010_4_2025MoreComplete_files/defaultAvatar.7e5c73d2.png"></div><div class="BotHeader_textContainer__kVf_I"><p>BotORFQ3TYM2O</p></div></a></div></div></div><div class="ChatMessage_messageRow__DHlnq"><div></div><div class="ChatMessage_messageWrapper__4Ugd6"><div class="Message_rowWithFooter__FShU6"><div class="Message_row__ug_UU"><div class="Message_messageBubbleWrapper__sEq8z"><div class="Message_leftSideMessageBubble__VPdk6"><div class="Message_messageTextContainer__w64Sc"><div class="Message_selectableText__SQ8WH"><div class="Markdown_markdownContainer__Tz3HQ"><div class="Prose_prose__7AjXb Prose_presets_prose__H9VRM Prose_presets_theme-hi-contrast__LQyM9"><p><em>I
