pretty solid. If we can’t even accept that, I’m not sure how society 
could keep going.<br>
Whether we believe in morality or not, we use faith every day. Faith is 
trusting in something we don’t know for certain. If all of our knowledge
 is based in uncertainty some micro-particle of faith must be used in 
every piece of knowledge we possess. Are we real or not? Do we have 
free-will or not? Is there a moral law or not? Ultimately, we’re blind 
to much of the foundational information that’s required to make 
