YouTube alone. How much more impossible would it be to try to learn all 
of the knowledge on the internet? Keep in mind all of the information on
 the internet is a simple re-telling or re-combination of phenomena that
 has already existed in the universe. How many more lifetimes would it 
take to learn all of the possible combinations of information the 
universe has to offer as a whole?<br>
The only way to continue in our progression as a species is if we 
continue to trust one another. We cannot learn everything there is to 
offer individually. A single person cannot learn astrophysics, machine 
learning, architecture, how to be a car salesman, farming, gene therapy,
 and every other discipline known to man. We were only able to gain 
these achievements as a society by having faith in each other and faith 
in the foundational laws of the universe namely belief in reality, free 
will, and moral law.</p>
<p>This being said, I am not advocating for the perpetual continuance of
 blind faith. Naivete is not a virtue. It is necessary to pursue 
